About Bowling Simulator

Project

This bowling simulator allows users to simulate bowling games and calculate scores.
Github:

Tech Stack

Frontend

  • React: JavaScript library for building the user interface and components
  • React Router: Enables navigation and routing between different views
  • CSS3: Used for styling components and creating responsive layouts

API Layer

  • RESTful API: Architecture pattern for client-server communication
  • JSON: Data format used for exchanging information between frontend and backend
  • CORS: Enables secure cross-origin requests between frontend and backend

Backend

  • JavaScript: Programming language used for server-side logic
  • BowlingGame class: Core logic implementation that handles game state and scoring

API Endpoints

Endpoint Method Description
/api/simulateRoll POST Simulates a single bowling roll
/api/simulateGame POST Simulates an entire bowling game
/api/resetGame POST Resets the game state
/api/undoRoll POST Undoes the last roll
/api/gameState GET Retrieves the current game state
); } export default AboutPage;
